The paper deals with distributed algorithms for wireless networks, which suggests that it could belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. The focus on broadcasting and communication graphs suggests that it could also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. The use of the SINR model and the analysis of time and lower bounds suggest that it could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SI) categories.
